<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6274&amp;p=59870#p59870</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6274&amp;p=59870#p59870"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Tile, Background Must-Have Tools For MS-DOS 6.22]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6274&amp;p=59870#p59870"><![CDATA[
TASM is an assembler which runs on 16-bit DOS.  It covers a lot of different processors.  You need to tell it you want 6502 mode with the -t65 switch, and make it output binary files with the -b switch.<br /><br />You may need a hex editor, like Hexit.  Not sure if it's 16-bit compatible or not.<br /><br />Tile Layer is 32-bit dos only.<br /><br />I don't know of any good 16-bit NES emulators for DOS, I think they're all 32-bit.  I know that NO$GMB is 286 compatible, but that's a Gameboy emulator.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=53">Dwedit</a> — Fri Apr 09, 2010 10:52 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
